-// format_score (5_000 → "5k", 5e6 → "5m").
+// History trail of what was wrong and what this fixes:
+//   - v1 (patch 0010): row-per-rarity layout. Bad on tall collections.
+//   - v2 (patch 0022): single-source-of-truth state. Right state, bad UI.
+//   - v3 (patch 0023): always-render Pokédex cells. Fixed layout corruption
+//     but kept the cramped 50px cells with count text BELOW the sprite.
+//   - v3.5 (patch 0027): tried to move count badge to top-right and hide
+//     scrollbar when content fit. Two bugs:
+//       a) badge was drawn BEFORE sprite, so the sprite drew on top of it
+//          → user reported "counts gone, looks like 1 of each".
+//       b) hide-scrollbar combined with the 650px ScrollContainer height
+//          made the panel exceed typical viewports while ScrollContainer
+//          thought everything fit (content ≈ 580 < 650) — so the bar
+//          stayed hidden and there was no way to scroll to off-screen
+//          content. User reported "scrollbar gone, can't scroll".
 //
-// Patch 0010 changes from v1:
-//   - True multi-col grid (was: row-per-rarity HContainer).
-//   - Drops `Game::should_render_title_ui()` gate — panel must stay open
-//     when the player enters the game. Lives in other_ui_window now.
+// v4 redesign rules:
+//   1. Cells 60w × 80h with petal sprite on top, name label at bottom,
+//      "x##" count badge in top-right. Badge drawn LAST so it always
+//      reads over the sprite.
+//   2. ScrollContainer max_height = 400. The grid (10 rows × 84px ≈ 840px)
+//      is always taller than the viewport — so the scrollbar is always
+//      live and the wheel always works. About half the grid is visible at
+//      once; the rest is one wheel-tick away. Better than a panel that
+//      "fits" in code but gets clipped by the browser edge.
+//   3. Header has three slots: Wipe (left), title (left, next to Wipe),
+//      Close (right). Click Wipe to zero all persistent_inventory; useful
+//      after a misclick filled a slot you wanted to keep empty, or just
+//      to start fresh.
+//   4. Petal name shown under sprite in 9pt with a thick stroke for
+//      readability on saturated rarity backgrounds.
+//   5. Click cell → equip via Game::equip_to_first_empty. Drag cell →
+//      drop on loadout slot via the existing patch-0015 plumbing.
 
